WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.268 --> 00:00:07.638
What can the African savannah
teach us about AI?

00:00:08.172 --> 00:00:09.673
Take this journey with me.

00:00:10.775 --> 00:00:12.543
Across Africa,

00:00:12.576 --> 00:00:15.546
proverbs are a cornerstone
of the oral tradition

00:00:15.579 --> 00:00:17.882
through which Indigenous
knowledge and wisdom

00:00:17.915 --> 00:00:21.318
has been passed down
from generation to generation.

00:00:22.219 --> 00:00:26.357
The Yoruba people of Nigeria
say that a proverb is the horse

00:00:26.357 --> 00:00:29.894
that can carry one swiftly
to the discovery of ideas.

00:00:31.062 --> 00:00:34.632
One of my favorite proverbs says,
when elephants fight,

00:00:34.632 --> 00:00:36.333
it's the grass that suffers.

00:00:36.867 --> 00:00:40.037
And it has guided me in making sense
of much in the world today,

00:00:40.071 --> 00:00:42.706
especially with all
the developments in AI.

00:00:43.407 --> 00:00:45.810
The elephants can symbolize great powers,

00:00:45.843 --> 00:00:48.746
be they nation states, corporations,

00:00:48.779 --> 00:00:50.448
broligarchies,

00:00:50.481 --> 00:00:52.750
while the grass comprises people,

00:00:52.783 --> 00:00:55.052
geographies and ecologies

00:00:55.086 --> 00:00:57.321
considered resources to exploit,

00:00:57.354 --> 00:00:59.623
wastelands or charity cases.

00:01:00.758 --> 00:01:03.461
Great power competition,
as we're living through today,

00:01:03.494 --> 00:01:06.230
emphasizes the power
of the metaphorical elephants

00:01:06.263 --> 00:01:10.734
in their quest for dominance
over resources, ideas and innovations.

00:01:11.669 --> 00:01:13.070
In the case of Africa,

00:01:13.104 --> 00:01:14.939
not only are we caught in the middle,

00:01:14.972 --> 00:01:16.607
but we comprise a key battleground

00:01:16.640 --> 00:01:18.776
over which elephants are fighting

00:01:18.809 --> 00:01:23.080
over natural and human resources
to power the intelligent age.

00:01:23.681 --> 00:01:26.684
Meanwhile, our perspectives and ambitions

00:01:26.684 --> 00:01:29.820
tend to be drowned out
by the din of the elephants.

00:01:30.855 --> 00:01:34.091
But what can we discover
when we look past the elephants fighting

00:01:34.125 --> 00:01:35.793
and zoom in on the grass?

00:01:36.527 --> 00:01:39.897
Well, for one, we can learn a simple
yet profound concept:

00:01:40.331 --> 00:01:43.134
I am because you are.

00:01:44.435 --> 00:01:46.303
This sums up a set of value systems

00:01:46.303 --> 00:01:49.306
that emerged among
the Bantu people of Africa,

00:01:49.340 --> 00:01:52.409
and is known as “utu” in Eastern Africa

00:01:52.443 --> 00:01:54.712
and “ubuntu” in South Africa.

00:01:55.880 --> 00:02:00.151
Utu and ubuntu instill in us
a profound appreciation of humanity

00:02:00.184 --> 00:02:02.153
as a quality we owe one another.

00:02:03.154 --> 00:02:06.323
And it's not just about
the relationship between humans.

00:02:06.357 --> 00:02:11.228
Ubuntu is also about our relationship
with nature and the spiritual or cosmic.

00:02:12.496 --> 00:02:16.600
Ubuntu reminds us we ought
to be developing technologies like AI

00:02:16.600 --> 00:02:20.104
for the benefit of all
of humanity and our ecology.

00:02:21.639 --> 00:02:26.377
Across Africa, we have exciting examples
of embracing the wisdom of ubuntu

00:02:26.410 --> 00:02:31.015
to inform data governance,
AI product design and community building.

00:02:31.916 --> 00:02:33.784
I call it ubuntech.

00:02:34.418 --> 00:02:35.586
(Laughter)

00:02:36.153 --> 00:02:40.624
AI development today treats data
as if it's an abundant natural resource,

00:02:40.624 --> 00:02:43.494
and we hear this in sayings
like, “data is the new oil.”

00:02:44.028 --> 00:02:46.897
But already the limits
of this paradigm are being realized,

00:02:46.897 --> 00:02:49.033
as researchers have been
sounding the alarm

00:02:49.066 --> 00:02:52.436
that high-quality data
to train AI models is drying up.

00:02:53.304 --> 00:02:57.041
Through ubuntu, we conceptualize
data differently,

00:02:57.074 --> 00:03:02.780
and we appreciate that it represents
lives, cultures and communities,

00:03:02.813 --> 00:03:07.885
so that data governance for us
is about the meaningful participation,

00:03:07.885 --> 00:03:11.155
informed consent, self-determination

00:03:11.188 --> 00:03:14.692
and community ownership
of data sets from which language,

00:03:14.725 --> 00:03:18.562
nature-based knowledge
and Indigenous wisdom are derived.

00:03:19.430 --> 00:03:20.564
(Applause)

00:03:20.598 --> 00:03:21.765
Thank you.

00:03:22.333 --> 00:03:25.135
And this has inspired
a concept like data justice

00:03:25.169 --> 00:03:26.971
in our African policy frameworks.

00:03:27.605 --> 00:03:29.240
Data justice matters

00:03:29.273 --> 00:03:34.411
because it means that women,
rural women in Africa, for example,

00:03:34.445 --> 00:03:39.116
who possess unique
knowledge about agriculture,

00:03:39.116 --> 00:03:41.185
food production, medicine

00:03:41.185 --> 00:03:42.987
and environmental protection

00:03:43.020 --> 00:03:46.357
are represented and visible
in data systems

00:03:46.390 --> 00:03:47.925
and agritech solutions.

00:03:49.093 --> 00:03:52.730
Then, when we've been told
ours are low-resource languages,

00:03:52.763 --> 00:03:54.531
we're resourcing our languages.

00:03:55.232 --> 00:03:59.169
Conventional AI wisdom
demands large language models,

00:03:59.169 --> 00:04:03.040
but African practitioners are making do
with little language models.

00:04:04.408 --> 00:04:10.214
See, driven by efficiency as a core value
and inspired by our relation to nature,

00:04:10.247 --> 00:04:15.653
initiatives like Lelapa AI have developed
lightweight African language models

00:04:15.686 --> 00:04:20.190
that are serving our communities
without requiring extensive resources.

00:04:20.891 --> 00:04:26.196
Their Inkuba small language model
has been inspired by the dung beetle,

00:04:26.230 --> 00:04:29.767
which can roll up to 250
times its body weight.

00:04:29.800 --> 00:04:31.969
It's small but mighty.

00:04:33.270 --> 00:04:36.573
Inkuba is trained
on 0.4 billion parameters

00:04:36.607 --> 00:04:40.344
and outperforms larger models
in sentiment analysis

00:04:40.377 --> 00:04:45.349
and displays remarkable consistency
across multiple languages.

00:04:46.183 --> 00:04:48.919
We're also building
collaborative AI communities.

00:04:49.620 --> 00:04:52.589
We have Masakhane, or building together,

00:04:52.623 --> 00:04:55.192
across over 30 African countries,

00:04:55.225 --> 00:04:58.295
to strengthen natural
language processing in our research.

00:04:58.595 --> 00:05:02.132
And this grassroots organizing approach
has set out to demonstrate

00:05:02.166 --> 00:05:05.703
that low-resourceness of languages
is not a data problem,

00:05:05.736 --> 00:05:09.273
but a societal one
best solved through participation.

00:05:10.140 --> 00:05:14.978
In fact, Masakhane have developed
a non-traditional authorship model

00:05:15.012 --> 00:05:19.049
that acknowledges and includes
all contributors in published papers.

00:05:19.416 --> 00:05:24.154
Be it that you contributed data,
lived experience, coded software

00:05:24.154 --> 00:05:26.357
or coordinated research participation.

00:05:27.024 --> 00:05:30.627
And this way, they've been able
to publish translation results

00:05:30.661 --> 00:05:33.297
for over 38 African languages.

00:05:34.531 --> 00:05:36.033
These examples of ubuntech

00:05:36.033 --> 00:05:39.169
are our way of charting
an alternative path

00:05:39.169 --> 00:05:42.639
to developing and deploying
AI solutions in Africa

00:05:42.673 --> 00:05:46.043
by Africa and beneficial for Africa.

00:05:47.044 --> 00:05:49.079
Ubuntech matters for a number of reasons.

00:05:49.913 --> 00:05:52.015
For one, we are asserting agency

00:05:52.049 --> 00:05:54.518
to conceive and build AI futures

00:05:54.551 --> 00:05:58.021
beyond just the ambition
of the metaphorical elephants

00:05:58.055 --> 00:06:00.190
and to contribute to a global commons.

00:06:01.558 --> 00:06:06.563
It also allows us to bring forward
the Indigenous wisdom of our ancestors

00:06:06.563 --> 00:06:09.933
so that ubuntech
is artificial intelligence

00:06:09.933 --> 00:06:12.436
powered by ancestral intelligence.

00:06:13.270 --> 00:06:18.308
(Applause)

00:06:18.342 --> 00:06:21.011
And we also get to remind the elephants,

00:06:21.044 --> 00:06:24.081
they may fight and wield
their might all they want,

00:06:24.114 --> 00:06:26.383
but they are also bound to suffer

00:06:26.417 --> 00:06:28.152
if they trample upon the grass

00:06:28.152 --> 00:06:30.988
to the point of irreparable
damage or extinction.

00:06:31.555 --> 00:06:35.559
But when their power is exercised
in relation to others,

00:06:35.592 --> 00:06:37.594
it makes them ecosystem engineers

00:06:37.628 --> 00:06:41.064
and redirects their energy
towards helping sustain a healthy

00:06:41.064 --> 00:06:43.400
and beneficial environment for everyone.

00:06:44.034 --> 00:06:45.969
And we see this in the savanna.

00:06:46.003 --> 00:06:50.641
When African elephants leverage
their power to trample upon dense shrubs

00:06:50.641 --> 00:06:51.975
and acacia trees,

00:06:52.009 --> 00:06:54.912
they make room for smaller
species to coexist.

00:06:55.312 --> 00:06:58.415
When they disperse seeds
as they trek across the land,

00:06:58.449 --> 00:07:00.317
they help generate new growth

00:07:00.317 --> 00:07:03.220
and maintain the biodiversity
of the savanna ecosystem.

00:07:03.720 --> 00:07:07.958
So in relationality, in coexistence,

00:07:07.958 --> 00:07:10.160
the power of the elephants is majestic.

00:07:10.194 --> 00:07:13.564
And it's a life force
for themselves, other wildlife,

00:07:13.597 --> 00:07:15.165
and the savanna ecosystem.

00:07:16.066 --> 00:07:19.603
I believe if we can reimagine humanity

00:07:19.636 --> 00:07:23.240
beyond just the ambition
of the metaphorical elephants,

00:07:23.273 --> 00:07:26.176
we can realize a world
that benefits everyone.

00:07:26.743 --> 00:07:28.679
So I implore all of you,

00:07:28.712 --> 00:07:31.448
take heed of the grass beneath your feet.

00:07:31.982 --> 00:07:34.785
Our collective future depends on it.

00:07:35.118 --> 00:07:36.286
Asanteni.

00:07:36.687 --> 00:07:42.392
(Cheers and applause)

